# Post-Deploy / End-of-Session Checklist

> **Inherited from CORE:** [checklist-protocol](docs/core-practices/documentation/checklist-protocol.md) — structural rules. [evolution/checklist-maintenance](docs/core-practices/evolution/checklist-maintenance.md) — when to add/remove a check.

Run this at the end of every session, including debug-only sessions. Skipping the Net Infra Footprint Check (§0) is a process violation regardless of session type.

---

## When to run each section

| Event | Required sections |
|-------|-------------------|
| Full feature deploy | All sections |
| Hotfix / targeted bug-fix deploy | §0 + §1 + §2 + §3 + §7 |
| Debugging session with no deploy | §0 + §3 + §4 + §7 |
| Infrastructure-only change | §0 + §1 + §3 + §7 |

---

## §0. Net Infra Footprint Check

Count and document the session's infrastructure delta.

- [ ] List every <infrastructure-resource-type> created, modified, or removed this session.
- [ ] Confirm each net-positive change had plan-mode approval before it was applied. Flag violations explicitly.
- [ ] Record the delta in the commit message.
- [ ] Record the delta in the active execution plan.
- [ ] Even when delta is zero, write `Net infra delta: zero` explicitly.

---

## §1. Infrastructure verification

Confirm all resources exist in the deploy target.

- [ ] <verification command for resource type 1> — confirm presence
- [ ] <verification command for resource type 2> — confirm presence
- [ ] <permission/role check> — confirm wired correctly
- [ ] <env var or config check> — confirm value reaches the runtime

---

## §2. Production smoke test

- [ ] Clear browser cache + service worker; hard refresh.
- [ ] Health/liveness endpoint returns healthy.
- [ ] Authentication flow completes with a test account.
- [ ] Each major <route/page/screen> loads without runtime error.
- [ ] Network requests in DevTools — no 5xx, no CORS errors.
- [ ] Test with one account per <user-role>.
- [ ] If an end-to-end suite exists, run it against the deploy target. Store results at `<artifact-location>/<YYYY-MM-DD>/`.

---

## §3. Documentation updates

- [ ] Active execution plan reflects current state.
- [ ] Affected specs and design docs updated.
- [ ] Build status table in `<CLAUDE.md>` reflects new counts.
- [ ] <project-specific doc 1> updated if scope hits its area.
- [ ] <project-specific doc 2> updated if scope hits its area.

---

## §4. Error log

Add an `ERR-NNN` entry to `<ERRATA.md>` if any of these occurred:

- Three or more failed fix iterations on the same problem.
- Misdiagnosis (root cause was not what was first hypothesized).
- Production breakage (any duration).
- Silent infra creep (resource shipped without plan-mode approval).

Use the template in `docs/core-practices/templates/project-scaffold/ERRATA.md.template`.

---

## §5. Machine/environment pitfalls log

- [ ] Add any new environment-specific gotchas to `<MEMORY-or-pitfalls-doc>`.

---

## §6. Quality grade refresh

- [ ] If a milestone closed this session, update the quality-score table.
- [ ] If a gap closed, strike through it in the functionality audit.

---

## §7. Session Reflection (Dream)

> **Inherited from CORE:** [evolution/dreaming](docs/core-practices/evolution/dreaming.md).

- [ ] Run the dream prompt at `docs/core-practices/evolution/dreaming.md`.
- [ ] Write the dream to `docs/dreams/dream-<YYYY-MM-DD>[-N].md` using the template at `docs/core-practices/templates/dream-report.md.template`.
- [ ] Confirm the dream names at least one concrete delta (or, if truly nothing diverged, says so explicitly).
- [ ] If five new dreams now exist since the last delta extraction, run the delta extraction prompt at `docs/core-practices/evolution/delta-extraction.md` and write `docs/deltas/delta-batch-<NNN>.md`.

